PRI synthetic fixture
=====================

`synthetic.pri` is a minimal hand-built fixture consumed by parser_test.go.
It is regenerated on demand by `TestRegenerateSyntheticPRI` (skipped by default;
run with `-pri.regen` flag).

Layout (little-endian throughout):

  Offset  Size  Field
  ------  ----  -----
  0       8     Magic = "mrm_pri2"
  8       4     Version = 1
  12      8     TotalSize (full file size)
  20      4     TocOffset = 32
  24      4     TocCount = 2
  28      4     SectionStart = 32 + 2*24 = 80
  32      24    TOC entry 0: name="[mrm_hsch]" + offset + size  (HSCH = names)
  56      24    TOC entry 1: name="[mrm_hsdt]" + offset + size  (HSDT = values)
  80      ...   HSCH section payload (3-string pool)
  ...     ...   HSDT section payload (3-string pool)

Each string-pool payload is:

  Offset  Size  Field
  ------  ----  -----
  0       4     Count = 3
  4       4     Entry 0 length in UTF-16 code units
  8       2*L   Entry 0 UTF-16LE payload
  ...     2     NUL terminator (0x00 0x00)
  ...     ...   Entry 1, 2 — same shape

Three string pairs are emitted:

  HSCH (names):  ["AppName", "AppDescription", "AppPublisher"]
  HSDT (values): ["Hello",   "World",          "Pri"]

Total file size is well under 4 KiB.
